        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 3:35PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 335 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hermitage, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hermitage, Wheatland, Macks Creek, Preston, Cross Timbers, Branch,
Leadmine, and Tunas.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
